Reading in and Filtering Data

eider<-read.csv(".\\data\\eider.csv")

Fox Occurrence GLM

Is there a relationship between arctic fox occurrence and number of eider nests?

Creating a Linear Model

model_fox <- glm(foxPresent ~ eiderNests, data=eider, family=binomial)
model_fox

Examining the Model

Model Coefficients

##  (Intercept)   eiderNests 
## -1.165332152 -0.003728512

Slope of Eider Nests variable is 0.003728512/4=.0009=.09%

For every unit increase in the number of eider nests, the probability of fox presence decreases by .09%. From this, we can only conclude that foxes are mildly afraid of eider nests.
